                                   Introduction
                                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
          This manual assumes you are familiar with the RISC OS desktop. You
          may want to read the Welcome Guide and the User Guide#url
          http://acorn.riscos.com/riscos3/37/37DiscImage/Manuals/Manual/BOOKB/
          BOOK_3.HTM> that come with your RISC OS system.
          You may also want to read this introduction to RISC OS.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    RiscMovie keeps track of your movie collection. For each movie you can
    set the genre, mediatype, audio tracks and subtitles. Each movie can have
    up to 3 titles (e.g. original and English).

    Multiple lists can be open at the same time and lists can be sorted and
    searched.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                      Previous
                                                                          Next
    ==========================================================================

                                   Installation
                                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      è   Download the program.
      è   The program is compressed into a Zip archive. Decompress it using
          e.g. SparkFS or Sparkplug#URL
          http://pilling.users.netlink.co.uk/free.html>.
      è   Copy the decompressed application, and any other files in the
          archive, to a place on your harddisc.
      è   That is it - you have installed RiscMovie.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                                      Previous
                                                                          Next
    ==========================================================================

                                     Starting
                                     ~~~~~~~~
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
          Use the interactive help to get help on specific icons and
          menuitems.
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Starting

                                                                        Page 1
    Doubleclick on the RiscMovie icon in the filer window to start RiscMovie.
    This will put an icon on the iconbar.

    Quit
    Select the Quit entry in iconbarmenu to quit RiscMovie. The ^Q shortcut
    also quits RiscMovie. If there is any data which has not been saved then
    RiscMovie will prompt you for confirmation.

    Creating a collection
    SELECT clicking on the iconbaricon will create a new collection and open
    a window showing that collection. From this window you can add and remove
    movies.

    Dragging an existing collection onto the iconbar icon will load it and
    display it in a new window.

    Configuration
    RiscMovie uses ConfiX to handle the configuration. For this to work the
    filer needs to have seen ConfiX. If you have installed ConfiX in
    !Boot.Resources it will happen automaticly at startup.

    ADJUST clicking on the iconbar icon will open the configuration window.
    Selecting Preferences in the iconbar menu wil also open the configuration
    window.

    The settings will only become active when saved. 
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
